MooseX-UserDaemon

VERSION

Version 0.05

SYNOPSIS

In your module:

    package YourApp;
    use Moose;
    with 'MooseX::UserDaemon';

    # MooseX::UserDaemon requires the consuming class to implement main()
    sub main {
      while (1) {
        ...
      }
      
      return '0 but true'; # Return '0 but true' on success.
    }

In your script:

    use YourApp;
    my $app = YourApp->new;

    exit $app->run unless caller 0;

On the commanline:

	Start your app
	$ myapp.pl start
		Starting...

	Check your status
	$ myapp.pl status
		Running with PID: ...

	Stop your app
	$ myapp.pl stop
		Stopping PID: ...

Or preferably in combination with MooseX::SimpleConfig and/or MooseX::Getopt:

In your module:
    package YourApp;
    use Moose;

    # Enable use of config file
    with 'MooseX::SimpleConfig';

    # Enable use of commandline parameters
    with 'MooseX::Getopt';

    with 'MooseX::UserDaemon';

    # '+configfile' Only required if using MooseX::SimpleConfig
    has '+configfile' => (
      is            => 'ro',
      isa           => 'Str',
      default       => $ENV{'HOME'} . '/.yourapp/yourapp.conf',
      documentation => 'Use custom configfile.',
    );

    sub main {
      while (1) {
        ...
      }
    }

In your script:

    use YourApp;
    my $app = YourApp->new_with_options;

    exit $app->run unless caller 0;

On the commanline:

	Start your app
	$ myapp.pl start
		Starting...

	Check your status
	$ myapp.pl status
		Running with PID: ...

	Stop your app
	$ myapp.pl stop
		Stopping PID: ...


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc MooseX::UserDaemon

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=MooseX-UserDaemon

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/MooseX-UserDaemon

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/MooseX-UserDaemon

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/MooseX-UserDaemon/


